title: For Sale:  Finn or Finnish Mosin M24
postcontent:
Collectors, here we have a Finnish made M24 Mosin Nagant rifle from my collection.

This is a true example of a battle veteran, that most likely saw lots of serious use and  could have been involved in at least two wars.

The rifle was assembled using a German made Bohler Stahl stepped barrel which retains it's original bluing and has an "96" dated antique receiver.

I would rate the bore at good or better and it is not counter-bored.

The two piece Finnish fingerspliced stock has some scars as should be expected, it also has some A's or M's stamps that indicate the butt portion at least, saw some Austrian use(World War1 ?), the handguard has the early copper rivets.

The barrel bands are an early type and are in great condition.

The bolt does not have matching numbers and is not that unusual on an issued and well used mosin. 

The sling and loops pictured were added by me and are not part of this sale.

Cleaning rod is part of the rifle and stays with it as it should.

This rifle is available for face to face sale in the Richmond, Henrico, Mechanicsville, Charles City and Hopewell areas.

This rifle would be a nice addition to most any Finnish or Mosin collection. 

Avoid all of the waiting, shipping charges, tranfer fees, and auction hassles. 

FTF $350.00
